# gen116 (rung 19) — bilingual ratchet for the autonomous act-loop. The same
# perceive -> decide -> act -> observe code path drives the loop from an Italian
# instruction: the agent competence lives in the algorithm, not in an English
# phrasebook. Italian carries the trigger words (parti da, raddoppia, finché,
# superi, dimezza, sotto); the canonical loop report stays English, exactly like
# the other reasoning modules (analogy.it, plan.it).

# "Start at 3 and double until you exceed 40" (superi = strict >): stops at 48.
> parti da 3 e raddoppia finché superi 40
< Reached 48 after 4 steps: 3 -> 6 -> 12 -> 24 -> 48.

# A shrinking loop in Italian: halve (dimezza) until below (sotto) 10.
> parti da 100 e dimezza finché sotto 10
< Reached 6.25 after 4 steps: 100 -> 50 -> 25 -> 12.5 -> 6.25.